# Cloudflare Pages redirects
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/

# app.wranngle.com is the canonical console host. The bare landing here
# (apps/ops-console/index.html, deployed to gtm-ops.pages.dev / gtm-ops.
# wranngle.com) was a marketing middleman — operators clicked through it
# to reach /console/. Redirect the entry-points to the new home so the
# middleman click goes away. Direct paths (/console/, /eval-runs/, etc.)
# still serve here as legacy aliases for any deep links already in the wild.
/                 https://app.wranngle.com/   301
/index.html       https://app.wranngle.com/   301

# Friendly alias for the legacy `/api/eval-runs` URL the UI used briefly
# before the canonical `/api/eval/runs` route landed in server.js.
/api/eval-runs    /fixtures/eval-runs.json    302

# Fallback for unported /api/* GETs in DEMO_MODE → fixture equivalent.
# (Pages Functions under functions/api/* take precedence — this only fires
# when there is no Function and the static fall-through misses. The JS shim
# in each HTML page also handles this client-side.)
/api/*            /fixtures/:splat.json       302
